National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with a delegation from the Syrian Opposition Coalition (SOC) at the White House. During the meeting, Rice reiterated the United States' commitment to supporting Syria's moderate opposition and explained that the US and partner nations' airstrikes in Iraq and Syria are aimed at targeting ISIL. Rice also emphasized that President Assad has lost all legitimacy, and the US remains dedicated to pursuing a negotiated settlement that ensures a genuine and inclusive political transition. The discussion focused on ways the US can support the moderate opposition to counter ISIL and enhance the chances of a political transition.